---
LetRec — every scope-block is a recursive scope.

`lower_module` (and any scope-block lowering) wraps the user's bindings
in a `·letrec` that declares all the user-bound names up front. Each
binding then fills its slot via `·set name, val`. Refs to any name in
the group resolve to a slot read; reading an empty slot traps at
runtime.

The rendered shape is `·letrec` followed by a single `fn slots: body`
— the slots are the params of a synthetic scope-fn, the body is the
sequence of `·set` calls and any other source-ordered statements.

Three motivations:

1. Uniform treatment of self-rec, mutual rec, and plain bindings —
   no SCC detection, no per-group special case.
2. Source-order side effects preserved — `·set` calls and any other
   effects fire in the order the user wrote them.
3. The slot semantics match the WasmGC lowering directly: nullable
   ref globals/locals, null-check on read.

Test format mirrors test_module.fnk.
---

{test, skip, expect, equals, cps_module} = import '!fake'
{ƒink} = import '@fink/parse/blocks.fnk'


---
Single binding — one slot, one set, then the publish/return chain.

Today's shape is `·let (i8 1), fn ·foo_0: ...`. Under LetRec the
chain becomes `·letrec fn ·foo_0: ·set ·foo_0, (i8 1); ...`.
---

test 'letrec single binding', fn:
  expect cps_module ƒink:
    foo = 1
  | equals ƒink:
    ·ƒink_module fn ·ƒctx_12, ·ƒret_1:
      ·letrec fn ·foo_0:
        ·set ·ƒctx_12, ·foo_0, (i8 1), fn ·ƒctx_15:
          ·ƒpub ·ƒctx_15, ·foo_0, fn ·ƒctx_17:
            ·ƒret_1 ·ƒctx_17, ·foo_0
    # sm:JgABAAcAAQAHJAEABxgBAAcSAAIABgEABwABAAcYAQADDgACAAoBAAcAAQAHDAAUAAQBAAMOAAYBDAEAAQABBgEAAQQACgAUAAIADgELAwABAAMQABQABAEAAw4ACgAUAAIAEgEAAwABAAMUABQABAEAAw


---
Two siblings — slots declared once, filled in source order.
Pub side effects interleave naturally.
---

test 'letrec two bindings', fn:
  expect cps_module ƒink:
    foo = 1
    bar = 2
  | equals ƒink:
    ·ƒink_module fn ·ƒctx_19, ·ƒret_2:
      ·letrec fn ·foo_0, ·bar_1:
        ·set ·ƒctx_19, ·foo_0, (i8 1), fn ·ƒctx_22:
          ·ƒpub ·ƒctx_22, ·foo_0, fn ·ƒctx_24:
            ·set ·ƒctx_24, ·bar_1, (i8 2), fn ·ƒctx_26:
              ·ƒpub ·ƒctx_26, ·bar_1, fn ·ƒctx_28:
                ·ƒret_2 ·ƒctx_28, ·bar_1
    # sm:PQABAA8AAQAPJAEADxgBEAcSAAIABgEPDwABAA8YAQADEgEQAw4AAgAKAQ8HAAEABwwAFAAEAQADDgAGAQwBAAEAAQYBAAEEAAoAFAACAA4BCwMAAQADEAAUAAQBAAMOAAoAFAACABIBEAcAAQAHDAAUAAQBAAMOAAYBDAEAAQABBgEAAQQACgAUAAIAFgELAwABAAMQABQABAEAAw4ACgAUAAIAGgEAAwABAAMUABQABAEAAw


---
Mutual recursion — `ping` and `pong` share a `·letrec` scope.
Each fn closure captures the sibling's slot by name; the slot
is filled by `·set` in source order.
---

test 'letrec mutual recursion', fn:
  expect cps_module ƒink:
    ping = fn x: pong x
    pong = fn x: ping x
  | equals ƒink:
    ·ƒink_module fn ·ƒctx_39, ·ƒret_4:
      ·letrec fn ·ping_0, ·pong_1:
        ·fn
          fn ·ƒctx_41, ·ƒret_6, ·x_2: ·pong_1 ·ƒctx_41, ·ƒret_6, ·x_2
          fn ·v_5:
            ·set ·ƒctx_39, ·ping_0, ·v_5, fn ·ƒctx_44:
              ·ƒpub ·ƒctx_44, ·ping_0, fn ·ƒctx_46:
                ·fn
                  fn ·ƒctx_47, ·ƒret_14, ·x_3: ·ping_0 ·ƒctx_47, ·ƒret_14, ·x_3
                  fn ·v_13:
                    ·set ·ƒctx_46, ·pong_1, ·v_13, fn ·ƒctx_50:
                      ·ƒpub ·ƒctx_50, ·pong_1, fn ·ƒctx_52:
                        ·ƒret_4 ·ƒctx_52, ·pong_1
    # sm:


---
Self-recursion — single name in the letrec group; the fn body
captures its own slot, which gets filled before any external
call to it can occur.
---

test 'letrec self-recursion', fn:
  expect cps_module ƒink:
    fib = fn n: fib n - 1
  | equals ƒink:
    ·ƒink_module fn ·ƒctx_27, ·ƒret_2:
      ·letrec fn ·fib_0:
        ·fn
          fn ·ƒctx_29, ·ƒret_4, ·n_1:
            ·op_minus ·ƒctx_29, ·n_1, (i8 1), fn ·ƒctx_31, ·v_8:
              ·fib_0 ·ƒctx_31, ·ƒret_4, ·v_8
          fn ·v_3:
            ·set ·ƒctx_27, ·fib_0, ·v_3, fn ·ƒctx_34:
              ·ƒpub ·ƒctx_34, ·fib_0, fn ·ƒctx_36:
                ·ƒret_2 ·ƒctx_36, ·fib_0
    # sm:RQABABUAAQAVJAEAFRgBABUSAAIABgEAFQABABUYAQADDgACAAoBDA8AAQAPCAAUABgBDAkWAQUBCgACABIBDgUAAQAFFgAUAAQBAAEKAAYBCAEAAQABBgEAAQQACgAYAQcFCgACABYBBwkAAQADEAAUAAQBAAkSAAQBCAUKABQBEw8KAAIAEgELFQABABUMABQABAEAAw4ABAEMDwoACgAUAAIAFgELAwABAAMQABQABAEAAw4ACgAUAAIAGgEAAwABAAMUABQABAEAAw


---
Mixed fn / val bindings — the LetRec slot list holds all module
names regardless of value shape. Later bindings can reference
earlier ones (filled slots); fn bodies can reference any sibling
slot because they're only invoked after all slots are filled in
straight-line tests.
---

test 'letrec fn val mixed', fn:
  expect cps_module ƒink:
    foo = fn x: x
    spam = 1234
    bar = fn y: foo y
  | equals ƒink:
    ·ƒink_module fn ·ƒctx_44, ·ƒret_5:
      ·letrec fn ·foo_0, ·spam_1, ·bar_2:
        ·fn
          fn ·ƒctx_46, ·ƒret_7, ·x_3: ·ƒret_7 ·ƒctx_46, ·x_3
          fn ·v_6:
            ·set ·ƒctx_44, ·foo_0, ·v_6, fn ·ƒctx_49:
              ·ƒpub ·ƒctx_49, ·foo_0, fn ·ƒctx_51:
                ·set ·ƒctx_51, ·spam_1, (i16 1234), fn ·ƒctx_53:
                  ·ƒpub ·ƒctx_53, ·spam_1, fn ·ƒctx_55:
                    ·fn
                      fn ·ƒctx_56, ·ƒret_14, ·y_4: ·foo_0 ·ƒctx_56, ·ƒret_14, ·y_4
                      fn ·v_13:
                        ·set ·ƒctx_55, ·bar_2, ·v_13, fn ·ƒctx_59:
                          ·ƒpub ·ƒctx_59, ·bar_2, fn ·ƒctx_61:
                            ·ƒret_5 ·ƒctx_61, ·bar_2
    # sm:


---
Three-way mutual recursion — extends the ping/pong shape to a
cycle of three slots. Each fn references the next; LetRec scales
beyond pairs without special-casing.
---

test 'letrec three-way mutual rec', fn:
  expect cps_module ƒink:
    a = fn: b
    b = fn: c
    c = fn: a
  | equals ƒink:
    ·ƒink_module fn ·ƒctx_47, ·ƒret_3:
      ·letrec fn ·a_0, ·b_1, ·c_2:
        ·fn
          fn ·ƒctx_49, ·ƒret_5: ·ƒret_5 ·ƒctx_49, ·b_1
          fn ·v_4:
            ·set ·ƒctx_47, ·a_0, ·v_4, fn ·ƒctx_52:
              ·ƒpub ·ƒctx_52, ·a_0, fn ·ƒctx_54:
                ·fn
                  fn ·ƒctx_55, ·ƒret_11: ·ƒret_11 ·ƒctx_55, ·c_2
                  fn ·v_10:
                    ·set ·ƒctx_54, ·b_1, ·v_10, fn ·ƒctx_58:
                      ·ƒpub ·ƒctx_58, ·b_1, fn ·ƒctx_60:
                        ·fn
                          fn ·ƒctx_61, ·ƒret_17: ·ƒret_17 ·ƒctx_61, ·a_0
                          fn ·v_16:
                            ·set ·ƒctx_60, ·c_2, ·v_16, fn ·ƒctx_64:
                              ·ƒpub ·ƒctx_64, ·c_2, fn ·ƒctx_66:
                                ·ƒret_3 ·ƒctx_66, ·c_2
    # sm:


---
Nested scope — local binds inside a fn body should also be in a
LetRec. The inner letrec declares `x, y` as slots; the outer
declares `foo`. Currently fn-body lowering still emits the flat
LetVal chain — only module scope is LetRec-wrapped.

# TODO: wrap fn bodies in LetRec too.
# Need: in `lower_fn` (and `lower_module_as_fn`), collect bind
# names from the fn's body sequence and wrap the lowered body in
# `ExprKind::LetRec`, analogous to `wrap_module_in_letrec` at
# module scope. Same `rewrite_lets_to_sets` pass converts the
# inner LetVals to Sets.
---

skip test 'letrec nested fn body', fn:
  expect cps_module ƒink:
    foo = fn:
      x = 1
      y = 2
      x + y
  | equals ƒink:
    Pending


---
Nested mutual recursion — two fns defined inside a fn body that
call each other. The inner letrec scope must declare both slots
so each closure can capture the other's slot.

Currently fails (see nested-fn-body TODO above) — without the
inner letrec, `inner-a`/`inner-b` are bound by sequential LetVal,
so the first closure can't see the second's slot.
---

skip test 'letrec nested mutual rec', fn:
  expect cps_module ƒink:
    foo = fn:
      inner-a = fn: inner-b
      inner-b = fn: inner-a
      inner-a
  | equals ƒink:
    Pending


---
Realistic mutual recursion with base cases — `is-even` and
`is-odd` call each other via slot reads, with a `match` base
case that terminates. Demonstrates that the slot model composes
with the match-arm machinery and supports terminating mutual rec
in real code (not just the trivial infinite-loop ping/pong).
---

test 'letrec is-even is-odd', fn:
  expect cps_module ƒink:
    is-even = fn n:
      match n:
        0: true
        _: is-odd n - 1

    is-odd = fn n:
      match n:
        0: false
        _: is-even n - 1
  | equals ƒink:
    ·ƒink_module fn ·ƒctx_197, ·ƒret_4:
      ·letrec fn ·is-even_0, ·is-odd_1:
        ·fn
          fn ·ƒctx_199, ·ƒret_6, ·n_2:
            ·fn
              fn ·ƒctx_200, ·ƒret_27: ·ƒret_27 ·ƒctx_200, true
              fn ·v_31:
                ·fn
                  fn ·ƒctx_202, ·ƒsucc_9, ·ƒfail_10, ·v_8:
                    ·fn
                      fn ·ƒctx_203: ·v_31 ·ƒctx_203, ·ƒsucc_9
                      fn ·v_37:
                        ·fn
                          fn ·ƒctx_205, ·ƒsucc_13, ·ƒfail_14, ·v_12:
                            ·op_eq ·ƒctx_205, ·v_12, (i8 0), fn ·ƒctx_207, ·v_17:
                              ·if ·v_17,
                                fn: ·ƒsucc_13 ·ƒctx_207
                                fn: ·ƒfail_14 ·ƒctx_207
                          fn ·v_25: ·v_25 ·ƒctx_202, ·v_37, ·ƒfail_10, ·v_8
                  fn ·v_43:
                    ·fn
                      fn ·ƒctx_211, ·ƒret_48:
                        ·op_minus ·ƒctx_211, ·n_2, (i8 1), fn ·ƒctx_213, ·v_52:
                          ·is-odd_1 ·ƒctx_213, ·ƒret_48, ·v_52
                      fn ·v_59:
                        ·fn
                          fn ·ƒctx_215, ·ƒsucc_45, ·ƒfail_46, ·v_44: ·v_59 ·ƒctx_215, ·ƒsucc_45
                          fn ·v_64:
                            ·fn
                              fn ·ƒctx_217, ·ƒret_66, ·v_65:
                                ·v_43
                                  ·ƒctx_217
                                  ·ƒret_66
                                  fn ·ƒctx_219:
                                    ·v_64
                                      ·ƒctx_219
                                      ·ƒret_66
                                      fn ·ƒctx_221: ·panic ·ƒctx_221
                                      ·v_65
                                  ·v_65
                              fn ·v_76: ·v_76 ·ƒctx_199, ·ƒret_6, ·n_2
          fn ·v_5:
            ·set ·ƒctx_197, ·is-even_0, ·v_5, fn ·ƒctx_225:
              ·ƒpub ·ƒctx_225, ·is-even_0, fn ·ƒctx_227:
                ·fn
                  fn ·ƒctx_228, ·ƒret_93, ·n_3:
                    ·fn
                      fn ·ƒctx_229, ·ƒret_114: ·ƒret_114 ·ƒctx_229, false
                      fn ·v_118:
                        ·fn
                          fn ·ƒctx_231, ·ƒsucc_96, ·ƒfail_97, ·v_95:
                            ·fn
                              fn ·ƒctx_232: ·v_118 ·ƒctx_232, ·ƒsucc_96
                              fn ·v_124:
                                ·fn
                                  fn ·ƒctx_234, ·ƒsucc_100, ·ƒfail_101, ·v_99:
                                    ·op_eq ·ƒctx_234, ·v_99, (i8 0), fn ·ƒctx_236, ·v_104:
                                      ·if ·v_104,
                                        fn: ·ƒsucc_100 ·ƒctx_236
                                        fn: ·ƒfail_101 ·ƒctx_236
                                  fn ·v_112: ·v_112 ·ƒctx_231, ·v_124, ·ƒfail_97, ·v_95
                          fn ·v_130:
